主要翻译
 
fatal adj (deadly, causing death)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 致命的 zhì mìng de  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 致死的 zhì mìng de ，zhì sǐ de 
 -- The driver's injuries proved fatal.
 
fatal adj (fateful)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 命里注定的，命运安排的，在劫难逃的 mìng lǐ zhù dìng de ，mìng yùn ān pái de ，zài jié nán táo de  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 重大的，决定性的 zhòng dà de ，jué dìng xìng de TC Traditional Chinese 決定性的 
 -- None of them would ever forget the events of that fatal day.
 
fatal adj (disastrous, destructive)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 灾难性的 zāi nàn xìng de TC Traditional Chinese 災難性的  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 毁灭性的 zāi nàn xìng de ，huǐ miè xìng de TC Traditional Chinese 毀滅性的 
 -- The loss of the grant was fatal to the project.

复合形式： 
 
nonfatal, non-fatal adj (not causing death)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 非致命性的 fēi zhì mìng xìng de  
 "" 
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 不致命的 fēi zhì mìng xìng de，bú zhì mìng de 
 
tragic flaw, fatal flaw n (literature)
           --> SC Simplified Chinese 悲剧性的缺陷  

